### 1.3 Role and Context Usage



In Scenario B (Professional Email), role assignment and context setting significantly improved the quality of the output. By specifying that the email should be professional and courteous, the model adopted the appropriate tone for communicating with a hiring manager. Providing context that the offer was being declined because another opportunity had been accepted helped generate a more realistic and transparent response.



In **Scenario C (Creative Content)**, adding context about the target audience (Gen-Z consumers living in Tier 1 cities) and specifying the desired tone (funny, culturally relevant, and using Gen-Z lingo) resulted in much more engaging and effective taglines. The additional context helped the model create content that was tailored to the intended audience rather than producing generic marketing slogans.



Overall, role assignment guided the style and tone of the responses, while context setting provided the model with the background information needed to generate more relevant, targeted, and higher-quality outputs.
